> Therefore, the mythical object called a "Noise Diode" does not
> exist.

That's like saying an "Amplification Transistor" doesn't exist. All
transistors amplify - some are better for this than others (some
are intended more for switching, etc.) Still, data sheets wouldn't
call them "Amplification Transistors".

A "Noise Diode" is a diode _being used_ to produce noise.
